    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven and cook for an initial 25 min</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cod-red-pepper-and-cherry-tomato-bake/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and cut your <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Peel and roughly chop your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Pick your <strong>basil leaves</strong> from the <strong>stalks </strong>(you'll be using both)</p><p>Cut your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cod-red-pepper-and-cherry-tomato-bake/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>pepper[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>in half (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and slice into long strips</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cod-red-pepper-and-cherry-tomato-bake/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>onion wedges</strong>,<strong> sliced pepper </strong>and<strong> chopped garlic</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cod-red-pepper-and-cherry-tomato-bake/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>halved</strong> <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong>, <strong>basil stalks </strong>(you'll use the leaves later!) and <strong>dried oregano</strong> to the pan</p><p>Add in your <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock mix</strong> and season with a good grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Cook for a further 2 min, stirring regularly</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cod-red-pepper-and-cherry-tomato-bake/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have had an initial 25 min, add the <strong>vegetables</strong> and any <strong>remaining juices</strong> from the pan into the <strong>oven-proof dish</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cod-red-pepper-and-cherry-tomato-bake/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Pat your <strong>cod fillet[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper and season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, then add them to the vegetables and push them down slightly</p><p>Return the dish to the oven for 12-15 min or until the potatoes are fork-tender and the cod is cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>cod</strong>,<strong> red pepper & cherry tomato bake</strong></p><p>Tip: Your cod is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cod-red-pepper-and-cherry-tomato-bake/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Tear the <strong>basil leaves</strong> roughly</p><p>Serve the <strong>cod</strong>,<strong> red pepper & cherry tomato bake</strong> and garnish with the<strong> torn basil leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
